<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-01-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in
                                        Japan,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Kanagawa,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-01-21"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 21, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> If the gunboat has not sailed, I hope
                            immediate clearance will be granted, as no unsettled difficulties exist
                            between Japan and any treaty power.</p>
                        <p>I have honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>ROBERT H. PRUYN.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>